.TH DU 1 "2026-05-18" "OurOS" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
du \- estimate file space usage
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B du
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIFILE\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Summarize disk usage of the set of FILEs, recursing into directories.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-human\-readable\fR
Print sizes in human-readable format (e.g. 1K, 234M, 2G).
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-summarize\fR
Display only a total for each argument.
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-all\fR
Write counts for all files, not just directories.
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-max\-depth\fR=\fIN\fR
Print total for a directory only if it is N or fewer levels deep.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-total\fR
Produce a grand total.
.TP
\fB\-\-exclude\fR=\fIPATTERN\fR
Exclude files matching PATTERN.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
du -sh /home/user        Summary of home directory
du -h --max-depth=1 .    Show immediate subdirectory sizes
du -ch *.log             Sizes of log files with total
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR df (1),
.BR ls (1)
.SH AUTHOR
OurOS Contributors.
